collections.name: BurnToEarn
collections.description:
The New gods Are the Cruelest: Once, gods demanded devotion. 
Chief among them is The Almighty Liquidity, a god not of mercy, but of motion. It does not rest, does not forgive, does not remember. It demands offerings, and blind faith. Its most devout servants burn the savings of their ancestors, praying for its favor...before being consumed by the very forces they worship.

He performs the ancient rite in a language of speculation. His relic, a machine pulsing with fire, channels the ritual. His sacrifice is not mere currency, but his very labor, stripped of its meaning, fed to the ever-hungry flames. "Burn some to make some."
The cycle repeats. The gods are indifferent.

collections.name: FloWar
collections.description:
IT grew, without reason, in a world of calculation, predictions, and data-hungry machines. A world where markets ruled, and every fluctuation dictated survival.

Around it, beings lived in harmony with an ancient machines. Born from an unpredictable evolution, these creatures had developed an unparalleled division of labour, blending instinct and algorithms. But one thing eluded them: the meaning of this simple flower that, against all logic, kept growing, impervious to price signals, fluctuations, and complex strategies.

Was it an anomaly? A glitch in the universe of probabilities?

The creatures split into factions. Some saw it as a mystery to unravel, a key to an ancient truth. Others, more pragmatic, saw it as a threat. Something that defied logic must be eradicated.

And so, war broke out. FloWAr.

This NFT combines digital ownership with a real-world asset (a physical handcrafted artwork). It is built on the ERC721 standard contract and is the only piece in the entire collection, making it one-of-a-kind.
